She resisted the forced romance of Algar, and God made him fall off a horse while Frithuswith was escaping. Later, she prays for water to sustain nuns in Binsey, and it rises from the ground. The well was/is a famous and important place of pilgrimage. Her shrine was St Frithuswith's Priory, which became Christ Church Cathedral. A shrine and chapel are dedicated to her today, and an Edward Burnes-Jones stained glass window represents her. For Opening times, see: http://goo.gl/2TnhEj --- For Music List, see: http://goo.gl/kq73UP

Patron saint is Lawrence: When his bishop, Sixtus, was denounced to the hostile pagan authorities, Laurence was put in charge of the church’s valuables, which he in turn entrusted to the poor of his congregation. Finally arrested, and charged to disclose the whereabouts of the church assets, Laurence showed the authorities the poor and sick of the church, saying, ‘Behold, here are the treasures of Christ’s Church’. Laurence was thus martyred for his refusal to comply by being roasted on a bed of hot iron bars.
properties.name: St Lawrence Church, South Hinksey
